f=\"mailto:cancellation@in.musafir.com?Subject=Cancellation/%20Amendment\" target=\"_top\">cancellation@in.musafir.com</a>. Musafir.com shall not be accountable to entertain any cancellation requests made through any other medium.\r\n\r\n38. For cancellation request within 48 hours prior to your scheduled flight departure, passenger should call us at <strong><em>+91-22-33951010</em></strong> or directly contact the respective airline.\r\n\r\n39. Few airlines do not allow amendments or cancellations within 48 hours of the schedule flight departure and treats the booking as a ‘No Show’.\r\n\r\n40. Musafir.com India cannot process cancellation of few airline tickets. In such cases, passengers have to directly get in touch with the airline. The cancellation depends on the airline terms and conditions.\r\n\r\n41. There will be no-refund for ‘no-show’ or any partially unused flights.\r\n\r\n42. Musafir.com India will levy Rs 649 per passenger and per sector for international flight ticket cancellation. This fee will be over and above the cancellation fee levied by the airline.\r\n\r\n43. If you have done a \'Web/Tele Check-in\' with the airline, you have to get in touch with the airline for cancellation. Musafir.com India will not be able to cancel your international air ticket in this case.\r\n\r\n<strong>Refund policy:</strong>\r\n\r\n44. You have to contact Musafir.com India for your international air ticket refund for bookings made by Musafir.com India as the respective airline will not be able to process your refund.\r\n\r\n45. You have to inform Musafir.com India for cancellations made directly with the airline. You can do that by either email or phone within 48 hours of the cancellation with valid documentations to initiate the refund process by Musafir.com India.\r\n\r\n46. Musafir.com India shall be in a position to process customer refunds against international flight tickets only if the same have been refunded by the respective airline.\r\n\r\n47. There will be no refund for ‘no shows’ or any partially unused flights.\r\n\r\n48. No refunds will be made on the ‘Non-refundable’ fares.\r\n\r\n49. Convenience fee of Rs 399 for one-way international flight and Rs 499 for roundtrip international flights, paid at the time of booking is a non-refundable fee and same shall be applicable on all cancellations including any partial cancellation requests.\r\n\r\n50. Processing time for cancellations and refund requests may vary.\r\n\r\n51. The average refund process takes 2 working days. However, the refund amount will show in your account between 3-15 working days.\r\n\r\n52. For partially utilized flight tickets (One sector flown and other sector cancelled), the refund will take anytime between 25 working days to 6 months depending on the airline.\r\n\r\n53. If the international flight ticket is cancelled directly with the airline, the refund process will take anytime between 15 days to 6 months depending on the airline processing time.\r\n\r\n54. If you have done a \'Web/Tele Check-in\' with the airline, you have to get in touch with the airline for refunds. Musafir.com India will not be able to refund the amount.\r\n\r\n54. Musafir.com India will only be able to initiate your refund after receiving a receipt and/or confirmation of refund from the respective airline.\r\n\r\n55. Promo code discount and other discounts provided at the time of bookings will be deducted from the refund amount.\r\n\r\n56. The refund amount will be credited back to the same account from where the booking was confirmed.\r\n\r\n57. The on-board meal amount is non-refundable. However, in case the flight is cancelled by the respective airline the amount will be refunded.\r\n\r\n58. In case, the airline cancels the flight, full air ticket cost will be refunded to the passenger. This however, excludes the convenience fee charged by Musafir.com India at the time of booking.\r\n\r\n59. In case, the airline discontinues its flight operations, Musafir.com India wi